                            Anonymous
                            <span class="pull-right">12 days ago</span>
                            <p>This is not a racing sim, nor is it an arcade racer - this is a hybrid of the two. The good parts - there is a great sense of speed, which makes the ride very tense and exciting. This game also has above-average engine sounds and amazing damage detail. The bad parts are the controls and physics - often you will flip because of the tiniest bumps, your car will spin out because the game often can't tell how much you are turning or braking (even when using analog controls).</p>
